@.str.180 = private unnamed_addr constant [441 x i8] c"Once you beat the big badasses and\0Aclean out the moon base you're supposed\0Ato win, aren't you? Aren't you? Where's\0Ayour fat reward and ticket home? What\0Athe hell is this? It's not supposed to\0Aend this way!\0A\0AIt stinks like rotten meat, but looks\0Alike the lost Deimos base.  Looks like\0Ayou're stuck on The Shores of Hell.\0AThe only way out is through.\0A\0ATo continue the DOOM experience, play\0AThe Shores of Hell and its amazing\0Asequel, Inferno!\0A\00", align 1
@e1text = dso_local global ptr @.str.180, align 8
@.str.181 = private unnamed_addr constant [467 x i8] c"You've done it! The hideous cyber-\0Ademon lord that ruled the lost Deimos\0Amoon base has been slain and you\0Aare triumphant! But ... where are\0Ayou? You clamber to the edge of the\0Amoon and look down to see the awful\0Atruth.\0A\0ADeimos floats above Hell itself!\0AYou've never heard of anyone escaping\0Afrom Hell, but you'll make the bastards\0Asorry they ever heard of you! Quickly,\0Ayou rappel down to  the surface of\0AHell.\0A\0ANow, it's on to the final chapter of\0ADOOM! -- Inferno.\00", align 1
@e2text = dso_local global ptr @.str.181, align 8
@.str.182 = private unnamed_addr constant [493 x i8] c"The loathsome spiderdemon that\0Amasterminded the invasion of the moon\0Abases and caused so much death has had\0Aits ass kicked for all time.\0A\0AA hidden doorway opens and you enter.\0AYou've proven too tough for Hell to\0Acontain, and now Hell at last plays\0Afair -- for you emerge from the door\0Ato see the green fields of Earth!\0AHome at last.\0A\0AYou wonder what's been happening on\0AEarth while you were battling evil\0Aunleashed. It's good that no Hell-\0Aspawn could have come through that\0Adoor with you ...\00", align 1
@e3text = dso_local global ptr @.str.182, align 8
@.str.183 = private unnamed_addr constant [504 x i8] c"the spider mastermind must have sent forth\0Aits legions of hellspawn before your\0Afinal confrontation with that terrible\0Abeast from hell.  but you stepped forward\0Aand brought forth eternal damnation and\0Asuffering upon the horde as a true hero\0Awould in the face of something so evil.\0A\0Abesides, someone was gonna pay for what\0Ahappened to daisy, your pet rabbit.\0A\0Abut now, you see spread before you more\0Apotential pain and gibbitude as a nation\0Aof demons run amok among our cities.\0A\0Anext stop, hell on earth!\00", align 1
@e4text = dso_local global ptr @.str.183, align 8
@.str.184 = private unnamed_addr constant [406 x i8] c"YOU HAVE ENTERED DEEPLY INTO THE INFESTED\0ASTARPORT. BUT SOMETHING IS WRONG. THE\0AMONSTERS HAVE BROUGHT THEIR OWN REALITY\0AWITH THEM, AND THE STARPORT'S TECHNOLOGY\0AIS BEING SUBVERTED BY THEIR PRESENCE.\0A\0AAHEAD, YOU SEE AN OUTPOST OF HELL, A\0AFORTIFIED ZONE. IF YOU CAN GET PAST IT,\0AYOU CAN PENETRATE INTO THE HAUNTED HEART\0AOF THE STARBASE AND FIND THE CONTROLLING\0ASWITCH WHICH HOLDS EARTH'S POPULATION\0AHOSTAGE.\00", align 1
@c1text = dso_local global ptr @.str.184, align 8
@.str.185 = private unnamed_addr constant [618 x i8] c"YOU HAVE WON! YOUR VICTORY HAS ENABLED\0AHUMANKIND TO EVACUATE EARTH AND ESCAPE\0ATHE NIGHTMARE.  NOW YOU ARE THE ONLY\0AHUMAN LEFT ON THE FACE OF THE PLANET.\0ACANNIBAL MUTATIONS, CARNIVOROUS ALIENS,\0AAND EVIL SPIRITS ARE YOUR ONLY NEIGHBORS.\0AYOU SIT BACK AND WAIT FOR DEATH, CONTENT\0ATHAT YOU HAVE SAVED YOUR SPECIES.\0A\0ABUT THEN, EARTH CONTROL BEAMS DOWN A\0AMESSAGE FROM SPACE: \22SENSORS HAVE LOCATED\0ATHE SOURCE OF THE ALIEN INVASION. IF YOU\0AGO THERE, YOU MAY BE ABLE TO BLOCK THEIR\0AENTRY.  THE ALIEN BASE IS IN THE HEART OF\0AYOUR OWN HOME CITY, NOT FAR FROM THE\0ASTARPORT.\22 SLOWLY AND PAINFULLY YOU GET\0AUP AND RETURN TO THE FRAY.\00", align 1
@c2text = dso_local global ptr @.str.185, align 8
@.str.186 = private unnamed_addr constant [313 x i8] c"YOU ARE AT THE CORRUPT HEART OF THE CITY,\0ASURROUNDED BY THE CORPSES OF YOUR ENEMIES.\0AYOU SEE NO WAY TO DESTROY THE CREATURES'\0AENTRYWAY ON THIS SIDE, SO YOU CLENCH YOUR\0ATEETH AND PLUNGE THROUGH IT.\0A\0ATHERE MUST BE A WAY TO CLOSE IT ON THE\0AOTHER SIDE. WHAT DO YOU CARE IF YOU'VE\0AGOT TO GO THROUGH HELL TO GET TO IT?\00", align 1
@c3text = dso_local global ptr @.str.186, align 8
@.str.187 = private unnamed_addr constant [495 x i8] c"THE HORRENDOUS VISAGE OF THE BIGGEST\0ADEMON YOU'VE EVER SEEN CRUMBLES BEFORE\0AYOU, AFTER YOU PUMP YOUR ROCKETS INTO\0AHIS EXPOSED BRAIN. THE MONSTER SHRIVELS\0AUP AND DIES, ITS THRASHING LIMBS\0ADEVASTATING UNTOLD MILES OF HELL'S\0ASURFACE.\0A\0AYOU'VE DONE IT. THE INVASION IS OVER.\0AEARTH IS SAVED. HELL IS A WRECK. YOU\0AWONDER WHERE BAD FOLKS WILL GO WHEN THEY\0ADIE, NOW. WIPING THE SWEAT FROM YOUR\0AFOREHEAD YOU BEGIN THE LONG TREK BACK\0AHOME. REBUILDING EARTH OUGHT TO BE A\0ALOT MORE FUN THAN RUINING IT WAS.\0A\00", align 1
@c4text = dso_local global ptr @.str.187, align 8
@.str.188 = private unnamed_addr constant [165 x i8] c"CONGRATULATIONS, YOU'VE FOUND THE SECRET\0ALEVEL! LOOKS LIKE IT'S BEEN BUILT BY\0AHUMANS, RATHER THAN DEMONS. YOU WONDER\0AWHO THE INMATES OF THIS CORNER OF HELL\0AWILL BE.\00", align 1
@c5text = dso_local global ptr @.str.188, align 8
@.str.189 = private unnamed_addr constant [93 x i8] c"CONGRATULATIONS, YOU'VE FOUND THE\0ASUPER SECRET LEVEL!  YOU'D BETTER\0ABLAZE THROUGH THIS ONE!\0A\00", align 1
@c6text = dso_local global ptr @.str.189, align 8
@.str.190 = private unnamed_addr constant [434 x i8] c"You gloat over the steaming carcass of the\0AGuardian.  With its death, you've wrested\0Athe Accelerator from the stinking claws\0Aof Hell.  You relax and glance around the\0Aroom.  Damn!  There was supposed to be at\0Aleast one working prototype, but you can't\0Asee it. The demons must have taken it.\0A\0AYou must find the prototype, or all your\0Astruggles will have been wasted. Keep\0Amoving, keep fighting, keep killing.\0AOh yes, keep living, too.\00", align 1
@p1text = dso_local global ptr @.str.190, align 8
@.str.191 = private unnamed_addr constant [194 x i8] c"Even the deadly Arch-Vile labyrinth could\0Anot stop you, and you've gotten to the\0Aprototype Accelerator which is soon\0Aefficiently and permanently deactivated.\0A\0AYou're good at that kind of thing.\00", align 1
@p2text = dso_local global ptr @.str.191, align 8
@.str.192 = private unnamed_addr constant [329 x i8] c"You've bashed and battered your way into\0Athe heart of the devil-hive.  Time for a\0ASearch-and-Destroy mission, aimed at the\0AGatekeeper, whose foul offspring is\0Acascading to Earth.  Yeah, he's bad. But\0Ayou know who's worse!\0A\0AGrinning evilly, you check your gear, and\0Aget ready to give the bastard a little Hell\0Aof your own making!\00", align 1
@p3text = dso_local global ptr @.str.192, align 8
@.str.193 = private unnamed_addr constant [461 x i8] c"The Gatekeeper's evil face is splattered\0Aall over the place.  As its tattered corpse\0Acollapses, an inverted Gate forms and\0Asucks down the shards of the last\0Aprototype Accelerator, not to mention the\0Afew remaining demons.  You're done. Hell\0Ahas gone back to pounding bad dead folks \0Ainstead of good live ones.  Remember to\0Atell your grandkids to put a rocket\0Alauncher in your coffin. If you go to Hell\0Awhen you die, you'll need it for some\0Afinal cleaning-up ...\00", align 1
@p4text = dso_local global ptr @.str.193, align 8
@.str.194 = private unnamed_addr constant [160 x i8] c"You've found the second-hardest level we\0Agot. Hope you have a saved game a level or\0Atwo previous.  If not, be prepared to die\0Aaplenty. For master marines only.\00", align 1
@p5text = dso_local global ptr @.str.194, align 8
@.str.195 = private unnamed_addr constant [107 x i8] c"Betcha wondered just what WAS the hardest\0Alevel we had ready for ya?  Now you know.\0ANo one gets out alive.\00", align 1
@p6text = dso_local global ptr @.str.195, align 8
@.str.196 = private unnamed_addr constant [390 x i8] c"You've fought your way out of the infested\0Aexperimental labs.   It seems that UAC has\0Aonce again gulped it down.  With their\0Ahigh turnover, it must be hard for poor\0Aold UAC to buy corporate health insurance\0Anowadays..\0A\0AAhead lies the military complex, now\0Aswarming with diseased horrors hot to get\0Atheir teeth into you. With luck, the\0Acomplex still has some warlike ordnance\0Alaying around.\00", align 1
@t1text = dso_local global ptr @.str.196, align 8
@.str.197 = private unnamed_addr constant [311 x i8] c"You hear the grinding of heavy machinery\0Aahead.  You sure hope they're not stamping\0Aout new hellspawn, but you're ready to\0Aream out a whole herd if you have to.\0AThey might be planning a blood feast, but\0Ayou feel about as mean as two thousand\0Amaniacs packed into one mad killer.\0A\0AYou don't plan to go down easy.\00", align 1
@t2text = dso_local global ptr @.str.197, align 8
@.str.198 = private unnamed_addr constant [310 x i8] c"The vista opening ahead looks real damn\0Afamiliar. Smells familiar, too -- like\0Afried excrement. You didn't like this\0Aplace before, and you sure as hell ain't\0Aplanning to like it now. The more you\0Abrood on it, the madder you get.\0AHefting your gun, an evil grin trickles\0Aonto your face. Time to take some names.\00", align 1
@t3text = dso_local global ptr @.str.198, align 8
@.str.199 = private unnamed_addr constant [386 x i8] c"Suddenly, all is silent, from one horizon\0Ato the other. The agonizing echo of Hell\0Afades away, the nightmare sky turns to\0Ablue, the heaps of monster corpses start \0Ato evaporate along with the evil stench \0Athat filled the air. Jeeze, maybe you've\0Adone it. Have you really won?\0A\0ASomething rumbles in the distance.\0AA blue light begins to glow inside the\0Aruined skull of the demon-spitter.\00", align 1
@t4text = dso_local global ptr @.str.199, align 8
@.str.200 = private unnamed_addr constant [174 x i8] c"What now? Looks totally different. Kind\0Aof like King Tut's condo. Well,\0Awhatever's here can't be any worse\0Athan usual. Can it?  Or maybe it's best\0Ato let sleeping gods lie..\00", align 1
@t5text = dso_local global ptr @.str.200, align 8
@.str.201 = private unnamed_addr constant [354 x i8] c"Time for a vacation. You've burst the\0Abowels of hell and by golly you're ready\0Afor a break. You mutter to yourself,\0AMaybe someone else can kick Hell's ass\0Anext time around. Ahead lies a quiet town,\0Awith peaceful flowing water, quaint\0Abuildings, and presumably no Hellspawn.\0A\0AAs you step off the transport, you hear\0Athe stomp of a cyberdemon's iron shoe.\00", align 1
@t6text = dso_local global ptr @.str.201, align 8
